|| Ellerslie Racecourse, 3pm\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Roope Rooster knockout competition ===\nThe semi-final between [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] required extra time as it was tied 20\u201320 at the end of normal time. This was very rare as usually tied games were replayed. [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] went on to win 28\u201320.\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1931 Roope Rooster Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 5 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Roope Rooster Competition/Play in the First Round/Ponsonby Defeats City\n| page =13\n| work =New Zealand Herald| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20965\n| date = 31 August 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310831.2.121.1\n| accessdate = 27 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Ponsonby|| 24 || City || 12 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3:15pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 5 Sep || Devonport || 41 || Newton || 8 || Carlaw Park # 2, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 5 Sep || Richmond || 15 || Ellerslie-Otahuhu || 11 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 12 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title = Roope Rooster Semi-final/Marist Team Defeated/Devonport Takes Honours\n| page =12\n| work =New Zealand Herald| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20977\n| date = 14 September 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310914.2.117.5\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Ponsonby|| 28 || Richmond || 20 || Carlaw Park # 2, 3:15pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 12 Sep || Devonport|| 11 || Marist || 8 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3:15pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 19 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Devonport\u2019s Triumph/The Roope Rooster Final/Defeat of Ponsonby\n| page =12\n| work =Auckland Star| volume= LXII| issue= 223\n| date = 21 September 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19310921.2.137\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Devonport|| 34 || Ponsonby || 17 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3:15pm\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Stormont Shield ===\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | Stormont Shield Result\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 3 Oct<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Champion of Champions/Devonport Defeats Marist/An Easy Victory Gained\n| page =10\n| work =New Zealand Herald| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20995\n| date = 5 October 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19311005.2.139.4\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Devonport||25 || Marist || 6 || Carlaw Park #1, 3pm\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Senior Reserve Grade standings ===\nThe standings include the 'final' between [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] and [[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby]] which was a 5\u20135 draw. This meant Devonport won the title as they finished the competition with one more point that Ponsonby. A Round 11 result between [[Marist Saints|Marist]] and [[City Rovers|City]] is unknown as it was not reported in the newspapers while the score between Devonport and Ellerslie-Otahuhu in Round 12 is also unknown, though [[North Shore Albions|Devonport]] were the victor.\n{|\n|-\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=175 |Team\n!width=20 abbr=\"Played\" |Pld\n!width=20 abbr=\"Won\" |W\n!width=20 abbr=\"Drawn\" |D\n!width=20 abbr=\"Lost\" |L\n!width=20 abbr=\"For\" |F\n!width=20 abbr=\"Against\" |A\n!width=20 abbr=\"Points\" |Pts\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[North Shore Albions|Devonport United Reserves]]\n|12||9||2||1||149||48||'''20'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Ponsonby Ponies|Ponsonby United Reserves]]\n|12||9||1||2||163||63||'''19'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Richmond Bulldogs|Richmond Rovers Reserves]]\n|12||9||0||3||147||74||'''18'''\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Marist Saints|Marist Old 