port || W || Ellerslie-Otahuhu || L || Devonport Domain, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 13\n| 1 Aug || Devonport || CCD || Ponsonby || CCD || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 1 Aug || City || CCD || Newton || CCD || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 1 Aug || Marist || CCD || Ellerslie-Otahuhu || CCD || Papatoetoe, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 14\n| 8 Aug<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Championship to Marist/Fast Match With Devonport/Doubtful Tries Awarded\n| page = 12\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20947\n| date = 10 August 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310810.2.138.5\n| accessdate = 26 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Marist || 3 || Devonport || 3 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 8 Aug || Ponsonby || 6 || Richmond || 5 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 8 Aug || Ellerslie-Otahuhu || WBD || City || LBD || Ellerslie Racecourse, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 15 Aug<ref>{{cite news\n| title =League Football/Final in Reserve Grade\n| page = 13\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20953\n| date = 17 August 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310817.2.137.2\n| accessdate = 26 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Devonport || 5 || Ponsonby || 5 || Carlaw Park #1, 1:45pm\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Reserve grade knockout competition (Stallard Cup) ===\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1931 Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 5 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Roope Rooster Competition/Play in the First Round/Ponsonby Defeats City\n| page =13\n| work =New Zealand Herald| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20965\n| date = 31 August 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310831.2.121.1\n| accessdate = 27 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Ponsonby|| 31 || City || 2 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 5 Sep || Newton || 9 || Devonport || 3 || Auckland Domain, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2013\n| 5 Sep || Ellerslie-Otahuhu || L || Richmond || W || Auckland Domain, 3pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 12 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title = Roope Rooster Semi-final/Marist Team Defeated/Devonport Takes Honours\n| page =12\n| work =New Zealand Herald| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20977\n| date = 14 September 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310914.2.117.5\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Newton|| 18 || Marist || 15 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:45pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 12 Sep || Richmond|| 15 || Ponsonby || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 3:15pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 19 Sep<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Cup for Richmond\n| page =12\n| work =Auckland Star| volume= LXII| issue= 223\n| date = 21 September 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19310921.2.137\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Richmond|| 13 || Newton || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 1:45pm\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Charity day tournament and death of a player ===\nOn 31 October a Charity Day was held at [[Carlaw Park]]. It featured a Seven-A-Side tournament, an 'old timers' match, a match between the referees and [[St John New Zealand|St Johns Ambulance]], and several running races. The proceeds would all go to the [[St John Ambulance New Zealand|St John Ambulance Brigade]]. Mr. Samuel Harris of the [[Newton Rangers|Newton]] team collapsed and died from heart failure a few minutes from time in the final. He had played in their earlier matches and had participated in a running race but had complained of feeling too unwell to run again. He collapsed while running with the ball and despite immediate attention from members of [[St John New Zealand|St, John Ambulance]] he died almost immediately. The match was called off.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Football Tragedy/League Player Collapses/Death at Carlaw Park\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume= LXII| issue= 259\n| date = 2 November 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19311102.2.89\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref> Harris had joined Newton in 1930 and was originally from [[Hikurangi]]. His funeral was held in Hikurangi on 4 November.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Footballers Death/Funeral at Hikurangi\n| page =12\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume= LXVIII| issue= 21021\n| date = 4 November 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19311104.2.102\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | 1930 Charity Seven-A-Side Tournament Results\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 31 Oct<ref>{{cite news\n| title =League Football/Charity Day Gala/Tragedy at Curtain Fall\n| page =11\n| work =Auckland Star| volume= LXII| issue= 259\n| date = 2 November 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19311102.2.130\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n|| Ellerslie-Otahuhu A|| 21 || Ellerslie-Otahuhu B || 6 || Carlaw Park # 2, 1:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 31 Oct || Richmond || WBD || Marist || LBD || Carlaw Park # 2, 2pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 31 Oct || Ponsonby || 15 || Newton B || 5 || Carlaw Park # 2, 2pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 31 Oct || Newton A ||13 || City || 0 || Carlaw Park # 1, 2:25pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Round 1\n| 31 Oct || Devonport || 38 || Ellerslie-Otahuhu A|| 2 || Carlaw Park # 2, 2:25pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 31 Oct || Newton A|| 19 || Ponsonby || 5 || Carlaw Park # 1, 4:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | semi-final\n| 31 Oct || Devonport|| 16 || Richmond || 0 || Carlaw Park # 1, 4:30pm\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Final\n| 31 Oct || Devonport|| no result || Newton A || no result || Carlaw Park # 1, 4:30pm\n|-\n|}\n\n== Lower grades and other club matches ==\n=== Lower grade teams ===\nThe Mid-Week competition which was running once again was made up of nine teams. It was decided to allocate the Monteith Shield to the championship. This had formerly been awarded to the winner of the Senior grade champions, but as of this year the newly presented Fox Memorial Shield would replace it. The Waitemata (Endean) Shield would be awarded to the team scoring the most championship points in the second round, and the \"Nuko\" Cup to the winner of the two lower teams on the ladder.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Draw For Mid-Week Games/The Competition Trophies\n| page =14\n| work =Auckland Star| volume= LXII| issue= 140\n| date = 16 June 1931\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19310616.2.164\n| accessdate = 23 October 2019}}</ref> Marist were awarded the Davis Shield for scoring the most competition points in the junior grades.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =League Football/Junior Management/Abuse of Players' Passes\n| page = 16\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume= LXII| issue= 243\n| date = 14 October 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19311014.2.158\n| accessdate = 28 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nGrades were made of the following teams with the winning team in bold:\n*'''Senior Reserve Grade''': City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Marist, Newton, Ponsonby, Richmond\n*'''Second Grade''': City, Mangere, Mount Albert, Mount Wellington, Northcote, '''Papakura''', Point Chevalier, Ponsonby (Papakura won the knockout competition)\n*'''Third Grade Open''': Devonport, Ellerslie, Glen Lynn, '''Marist''', Papatoetoe, Ponsonby, Richmond (Marist won after beating Ponsonby 4\u20132 in the final, while Ponsonby won the knockout final 8\u20132 over Marist)\n*'''Third Grade Intermediate''': Akarana, City, Glen Lynn, Glenora, Marist, Mount Albert, Ponsonby, '''Richmond''' (Richmond won the championship and knockout competition)\n*'''Fourth Grade''': Akarana, Avondale, City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Glen Lynn, '''Marist''', Mount Albert, Mount Wellington, Newmarket, Northcote, Papakura, Papatoetoe, Point Chevalier, Ponsonby, Richmond (Marist won the championship and the knockout competition)\n*'''Fifth Grade''': City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Glen Lynn, '''Marist''', Mount Albert, Newmarket, Newton, Northcote, Papatoetoe, Ponsonby, Richmond (Marist won the championship and the knockout competition)\n*'''Sixth Grade''': Akarana, City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Marist, '''Newmarket''', Newton, Northcote, Point Chevalier, Richmond (Newmarket beat Richmond 3\u20132 in the final)\n*'''Seventh Grade''': City, Ellerslie, Glen Lynn, Newmarket, Papatoetoe, Point Chevalier, '''Richmond A''', Richmond B (Richmond A won the championship)\n*'''Primary Schoolboys''': Avondale, City, Devonport, Ellerslie, Newton, Newmarket, Northcote, Papatoetoe, Parnell, Richmond A, Richmond B\n*'''Mid-Week Competition''': Auckland Loco, Birkenhead, City Markets, Green Lane, New Zealand Fertilisers, Nicholson Park, Post Office, Stonex and Stormont's, Town Board Rovers, Waterside Workers\n\n=== Other notable matches ===\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|+ class=\"nowrap\" | List of Matches\n|-\n|\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" |\n! scope=\"col\" | Score\n! scope=\"col\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" | Attendance\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 11 July<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Frequent Penalties/Teams Evenly Matched\n| page = 12\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20923\n| date = 13 July 1931\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19310713.2.143.2\n| accessdate = 24 October 2019}}</ref>|| Kia Ora (Huntly)|| 5 || City || 25 || Huntly\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Exhibition Match\n| 18 July<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Win for Devonport\n| page = 12\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume= LXVIII| issue= 20929\n| date = 2